BR> : has stolen 1 platinum 3 gold 9 silver and 30 copper <BR>  <BR> The second one: <BR> /smile <BR> : has picked your pocket <BR> : has stolen 9 gold 7 silver and 60 copper <BR>  <BR> I alternated these two with a few people.  I got one 31st level palidin. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://server2.ezboard.com:8080/uwidan.showPublicProfile>Widan</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC= http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_purplespot.gif  BORDER=0 HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10></span><br><font color=#FF0000>(8/21/99 12:37:46 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Torturing high level chars</span><hr size=1> The best way I know of to torture high level characters is to beg them for free stuff.  Don't leave them alone just keep begging.  Then pretend you are trying to offer then a deal.  &quot;Ok look,  I have 15 pp and this dragoon dirk,  with you give me that ebony bladed sword?  Cmon please?  Help a newbie oh cmon! pleeeeease&quot; <BR>  <BR> Soon you'll have the record for being on the most number of ignore lists! <BR>  <BR>  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://server2.ezboard.com:8080/bthesafehouse.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=cyric>Cyric</A></span><br><font color=#FF0000>(8/25/99 11:07:32 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Torturing high level chars</span><hr size=1> My god you aren't kidding, beggers drive me nuts. <BR>  <BR> Worse one was a low level rogue who bother me for days trying to get me to trade my SBD for rubicite pants, then bracers, then helm.   <BR>  <BR> I traded Rubicite greeves to a NON Rogue for my SBD and it was the deal of a lifetime.  Why then would I want to give up my most powerful weapon for rubicite anything.  Bother a non-rogue.... ack. <BR>  <p>-Cyric d'Veldrin
Lvl 32 Dark Elf Rogue, Veeshan
"A dagger in the dark is worth a thousand swords at dawn."</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://server2.ezboard.com:8080/bthesafehouse.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=sloren>sloren</A></span><br><font color=#FF0000>(8/25/99 11:15:55 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.boydshotrods.com/images/sloren.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Torturing high level chars</span><hr size=1> If they bug ya enough, tell em you have to get somthin out of the bank and lead then to an areana a kill them,,Never done this but have been tempted,,would it work. <BR> If ya beg from an NPC enough they kill ya, and most people quit begging from them after this happens a couple of times,,So it could make them think twice. <p><font color="#FF0000">Sloren, Humble Hafling of Tunare()<br>
</font><small><small><small><small><font color="#008000">Ok, Humble may not fit, allow me my
delusions, an I will allow you yours.</font></small></small></small></small></p>
</p><i>Edited by <A HREF=http://server2.ezboard.com:8080/bthesafehouse.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=sloren>sloren</A> at: 8/25/99 12:17:58 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://server2.ezboard.com:8080/ufreonsmurf.showPublicProfile>FreonSmurf</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC= http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_star.gif  BORDER=0 HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10></span><br><font color=#FF0000>(8/25/99 2:54:02 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Torturing high level chars</span><hr size=1> LOL <BR> Yes Sloren, you are a fine halfing women. Smart and cunning, and ya keep  your pockets filled with the biguns gold.  That idea is great, I usally hand out some nice shiny's, but next one on my coattails, I shall take them to the arena for a new definition of pain! <BR>  <BR> It would work, just say wait here, or take the long route and lead them thru it.  Or even better get them to use auto-follow.  They still get that little message they entered a pvp arnea.  Just depends on how dumb & greedy they are. <p>Wixramiablo Sneakypants
Covenant of Peace
