DeepPocket of Rodect Nife</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://server2.ezboard.com:8080/bthesafehouse.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=sloren>sloren</A></span><br><font color=#FF0000>(8/25/99 3:12:27 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.boydshotrods.com/images/sloren.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Torturing high level chars</span><hr size=1> *sloren smiles in an inocent fashion, then it changes to a wicked grin, eyes almost glowing with evil thoughts.* <BR>  <BR> Well don't take that previous post the wrong way, I am very kind to others, but every now and then, you get a pest you would like to get rid of. I will be tempted to try it next time I get hounded for free stuff, but I don't think I havethe heart to do it. <BR>  <BR> *well maybe just once,,, <p><font color="#FF0000">Sloren, Humble Hafling of Tunare()<br>
</font><small><small><small><small><font color="#008000">Ok, Humble may not fit, allow me my
delusions, an I will allow you yours.</font></small></small></small></small></p>
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://server2.ezboard.com:8080/ukoru.showPublicProfile>Koru</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalBlack.gif BORDER=0 HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10></span><br><font color=#FF0000>(8/25/99 6:20:27 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Hehe, get a load of this one then...</span><hr size=1> Ok, this was a while back but I still remember it clearly as it was the most annoying beggar I have ever had the displeasure of dealing with: <BR>  <BR> There I was, minding my own buisness at 16th level when I get a tell &quot;Will you group with me?&quot; Now, being a rogue that imediately made me suspicious so I do a who on the guy and, hmm, an 8rd level monk. I explain that he won't get any xp and neither will I for that matter. Ok, guy sends me a tell saying he's the brother of a guy I grouped with <b>twice</b> and then tells me he needs some help killing desert madmen and dervishes in N Ro. So I figure what the heck, I'll help him out with 1-2 of them. Get there, group with him and what does he say? &quot;I don't want the xp, I just want (all) the money and the gems they have&quot;. Um, and what am I getting from this partnership? Anything? Well, there comes the desert madman, attack, oops, there comes the mummy too, um, make that two mummies. Tell little idjut to run, idjut starts screaming for help, ok, get lucky and an 18th lvl paladin steps in and saves my sorry behind. Results? I'm diseased at 1 and half bubble, idjut monk is at 4 bubbles, paladin is perfectly fine and we have killed one mummy, which the idjut promptly loots (no auto-loot on for him of course). Then he starts going on about how he desperately needs gems. So I'm fed up at this point and leave. Next day: I have confirmed with the guy I grouped with that this is his little brother. So I get tell saying &quot;Will you buy me a lockjaw tunic?&quot;. I do a who on the guy and he's a 5th level monk. He then tells me he's the same guy from last nigit playing a different char. Then I tell him I'm not that rich. &quot;Ok, will you kill lockjaw and get me the tunic then?&quot; Um, me? Kill lockjaw at 16th? When I can hardly find groups in less than 3 hours and LJ is camped to hell? I think not. Ok, so he keeps going on and on about how he desperately <b>needs</b> the tunic so he can play his character. Yeah, right, just like I absolutely need an SBD to play my character. I try to explain all this to him. Results? &quot;Can you please help me get a lockjaw tunic?&quot; I explain more, I use simple words. Results? &quot;Can you come to Crushbone and help me kill things?&quot; At this point I'm through being nice, the idjut's brother was a nice enough person but enough is enough, no I'm not going to wait 2 hours for a boat that will crash so I can come over and bail your hide out after you try to attack Crush and DVinn expecting me to give all the loot we get to you. /ignore idjut. Ah, I love filters almost as much as I'd have loved killing him - but I wasn't going to go to Kaladim to do that. <BR>  <BR> Now these days when I get a tell like &quot;Can you give me and my friend a full set of banded?&quot; from a 2nd level, I just put them on ignore. I can't be bothered raising my blood preassure for them. I just wish we could do unlimited ignore - there seem to be unlimited idiot beggars after all. <BR>  <BR> K. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://server2.ezboard.com:8080/bthesafehouse.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=docgonzo>Doc Gonzo</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Local user</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(9/15/99 10:54:02 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Hehe, get a load of this one then...</span><hr size=1> I, having been born in Queynos, make it a point to return there every few levels (just a level 17 now anyway).   When I do I alway do a quick /who rogue to see who is the lowest level rogue in the area.   After a few (in character)  /tells I usually load the buggers up with a few items of loot (ABSOLUTELY NOTHING ALL THAT VALUABLE.)  Typical set will include: <BR>   <BR> 1 backpack  <BR> 2-3 pieces of rawhide armor  <BR> 1 decent weapon (nothing better than a normal steel rapier for instance -- and only given two of these away)  <BR> 1 or 2 Div Rings  <BR> 1 studded collar  <BR> 5 plats  <BR>   <BR> Made some great friends and been forgotten about after having do this.   Once, I /tell a brand new rogue ... playing time in EQ total?  less than 10 minutes ... we still talk and she's becoming a great friend.     <BR>   <BR> Others I wish I could remember their names cause I'd like to ask for a refund ;-)  <BR>  <p></p><i>Edited by <A HREF=http://server2.ezboard.com:8080/bthesafehouse.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=docgonzo>Doc Gonzo</A> at: 9/15/99 11:56:36 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://server3.ezboard.com/unattasha.showPublicProfile>Nattasha</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif BORDER=0 HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Global user</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(10/9/99 1:56:21 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> my favorite emote...</span><hr size=1> :is interested in making a trade. <BR> :is interested in making a trade. <BR> :is interested in making a trade. <BR>  <BR> i have it hot-keyed..its great if you do it where there are a bunch of casters sitting down <BR> makes everyone get up. <p>~ NATTASHA ~
